### TITLE ###
Interactive input basic
### DESCRIPTION ###
Typing fills the field and Enter submits. Frames capture the cursor moving as
each rune is appended, then the collapsed line echoes the answer.
### INPUT ###
print(input("Name > "))
### KEYS ###
"Alice"
enter
### STDOUT ###
Alice

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Name > █
--- frame 1 (A) ---
Name > A█
--- frame 2 (l) ---
Name > Al█
--- frame 3 (i) ---
Name > Ali█
--- frame 4 (c) ---
Name > Alic█
--- frame 5 (e) ---
Name > Alice█
--- frame 6 (enter) ---
Name > Alice
### TITLE ###
Interactive input backspace edit
### DESCRIPTION ###
Backspace deletes the rune before the cursor, so a typo can be corrected before
submitting.
### INPUT ###
print(input("> "))
### KEYS ###
"Bobb"
backspace
enter
### STDOUT ###
Bob

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
> █
--- frame 1 (B) ---
> B█
--- frame 2 (o) ---
> Bo█
--- frame 3 (b) ---
> Bob█
--- frame 4 (b) ---
> Bobb█
--- frame 5 (backspace) ---
> Bob█
--- frame 6 (enter) ---
> Bob
### TITLE ###
Interactive input default when empty
### DESCRIPTION ###
With a default set and nothing typed, the field shows the default as a
placeholder and submitting empty returns the default.
### INPUT ###
print(input("> ", default="guest"))
### KEYS ###
enter
### STDOUT ###
guest

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
> █Default: guest
--- frame 1 (enter) ---
> 
### TITLE ###
Interactive secret input
### DESCRIPTION ###
A secret input echoes nothing as the user types: every frame is identical and
the typed runes never appear in any frame, yet the real value still flows to the
script. No collapsed summary is left behind.
### INPUT ###
print(input("Password > ", secret=true))
### KEYS ###
"s3cret"
enter
### STDOUT ###
s3cret

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Password > █
--- frame 1 (s) ---
Password > █
--- frame 2 (3) ---
Password > █
--- frame 3 (c) ---
Password > █
--- frame 4 (r) ---
Password > █
--- frame 5 (e) ---
Password > █
--- frame 6 (t) ---
Password > █
### TITLE ###
Interactive input cancel
### DESCRIPTION ###
Ctrl-C aborts the input, surfacing as a rad error and a non-zero exit. No summary
frame is left behind on cancel.
### INPUT ###
print(input("> "))
### KEYS ###
"x"
ctrl-c
### STDERR ###
error[RAD20010]: Error reading input: input canceled
  --> <script>:1:7
  |
1 | print(input("> "))
  |       ^^^^^^^^^^^
  |
   = info: rad docs RAD20010


### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
> █
--- frame 1 (x) ---
> x█
### EXIT ###
1
